{"badges":["TM6"],"usefulItems":"glass jar with airtight lid","id":"r423446","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-4T7nu3JzSMI\/XZWZ9JyO7HI\/AAAAAAAAeUA\/hPnkCGuvF1kUW1F0T3CyaT28DZ5GFbh9wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_qcDsmOcjnyYyaCjq.png","title":"Caramelised Red Onion Chutney","publishedAt":"2019-03-09T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"25 g olive oil"},{"content":"500 g red onions, cut in wedges"},{"content":"½ - 1 fresh red chilli, thinly sliced, to taste"},{"content":"200 g light brown sugar"},{"content":"1 tsp fine sea salt"},{"content":"200 g red wine vinegar"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 Total recipe","carbohydrates":"221 g","calories":"5086 kJ \/ 1215 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Place oil and onions in mixing bowl then caramelise <b>High Temp.<b>  (see tip)."},{"content":"Add red chilli, sugar, salt and vinegar then cook <b>25 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 0.5<b>. While still warm, transfer to a glass jar with airtight lid (see tip), leaving approx. 5 mm. Make sure that the rim of the jar is clean, then seal immediately. Leave to cool completely then refrigerate for 1 day before serving. Store in the fridge for up to 1 month."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The high temperatures of Thermomix caramelise the red onions for a fuller flavour in this tasty chutney. Serve with goat’s cheese on crackers or crostini for a great canapé, or add to a cheese board.","If some caramelised onion sticks to the bottom of the mixing bowl, the vinegar in the next step will dissolve it almost completely.","To prepare jar, place <b>500 g<b> water in mixing bowl. Place jar and lid upside down in the centre of the Varoma and steam <b><b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.<b>  Leave to drain - do not dry or touch the inside surfaces. Alternatively, thoroughly wash jar and lids in hot, soapy water. Rinse by pouring over boiling water. Prepare for filling, if needed, by placing on a clean tea towel in a roasting tin and heat in the oven at 100˚C until required."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","24h","1"]}